The paper proposes a novel lip-reading driven deep learning framework for speech enhancement, which involves both audio and visual processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and speech processing (cs.SD). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed framework using objective and subjective testing methods, which could place it in the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
